org.hps.analysis.trigger

Class SimTriggerModule2019<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hps.analysis.trigger.SimTriggerModule2019<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - - The type of clusters from which the triggers were simulated. This will always be either Cluster or VTPCluster.

    public class SimTriggerModule2019<E>
extends Object
    Class SimTriggerModule2019 is a container class that holds simulated trigger results for each of the four primary triggers produced by the DataTriggerSimDriver2019. Class SimTriggerModule2019 is developed based on Class SimTriggerModule
    See Also:
    DataTriggerSimDriver

    • Method Detail

      • getSinglesTriggers

        public List<SinglesTrigger2019<E>> getSinglesTriggers(int triggerNumber)
        Gets the simulated trigger results for the indicated singles trigger. Note that only inputs of 0, 1, 2 and 3 are allowed.
        Parameters:
        triggerNumber - - A value of either 0, to obtain the singles 0 trigger results, or 1, to obtain the singles 1 trigger results, or 2, to obtain the singles 2 trigger results, or 3, to obtain the singles 3 trigger results.
        Returns:
        Returns the trigger results as a List of SinglesTrigger2019 objects.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Occurs if the input argument is not either 0 or 1 or 2 or 3.
